  "texts": [
    "Then since ∅ ̸ = ↓O -⊊ ↓O ⊆ p M, we have ∅ ̸ = φ M ⊊ p M.Hence there is an x with M, x ⊩ p ∧ φ and a y with M, y ⊩ p and M, y ⊮ φ, which by Refinability and Persistence implies that there is a y ′ ⊑ y with M, y ′ ⊩ p ∧ ¬φ.",
    "Thus, the formula ♢ i (p ∧ ψ) → ♢ i (p ∧ φ) ∧ ♢ i (p ∧ ¬φ) will be valid over F.Our strategy to define φ will be to define a polymodal formula α and appropriate accessibility relations of F for the operators in α such that if p M ∩ RO(R) = ↓O, then α M = ↓σ O -.",
    "We will also define an accessibility relation R ▷ such that α M = ↓σ O -implies ♢ ▷ α M = ↓O -.",
    "We can then take φ:= ♢ ▷ α.In addition to the universal relation R i, we will define four other accessibility relations for F. The relation R ▷ just mentioned only relates regular open sets to sets of pairs:• OR ▷ σ iff ∀⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩ ∈ σ ∃(a, b) ⊆ O: (a, b) ⊆ (a ′, b ′).",
    "For any O ∈ RO(R) \\ {∅}, OR ▷ σ O for σ O as in (2.3); and xR ▷ y only if x ∈ RO(R) \\ {∅}."
